                        <div class="muscle-text bd-bot exercise-list-start">
                            <h3><strong>Triceps Long Heads</strong></h3><p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">triceps long head</a> is one of three heads that make up the triceps brachii muscle. It originates from the bottom part of the shoulder blade and inserts into the forearm.</p><p>This muscle is particularly active during elbow extension (straightening) overhead. This makes the dumbbell single-arm tricep extension very effective at targeting the triceps long head. The stretch overhead increases the muscle’s activation, while the dumbbell provides more resistance, requiring it to work harder.</p><p>Electromyographic data studies show the triceps brachii can reach <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2017/07000/maximal_strength_performance_and_muscle_activation.15.aspx" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">40%–50%</a> of maximum activation during weighted tricep extension exercises. This shows how hard the muscle works during the dumbbell single-arm tricep extension.</p>                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
